body.description: Chrome Battery presents YTX9-BS sealed AGM batteries, the precision power solution. Each battery is constructed with lead calcium alloy and absorbed glass mat technology that allows for a complete maintenance-free and high-performance operation. Chrome Battery features improvements in the longevity, warranty, returns, and shipping over our other brands; Pirate and Zipp. All YTX9-BS Chrome Battery brand AGM batteries are manufactured with the highest quality materials and rigorously tested to ensure safety, OEM compatibility, effectiveness, and optimal performance. YTX9-BS is a 12V 12CCA High Performance Sealed AGM Battery. YTX9-BS has AGM Separators for superior design and durability.YTX9-BS Battery Features: No spills, no leaks, and no water to check. Extreme vibration resistance to ensure maximum conductivity. High Cranking Amps & Low Self-Discharge Rate. Fully charged, ready for immediate use. Fits in a variety of applications, ranging from motorcycles, ATVs, UTVs, jet skis, snowmobiles, scooters and more. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Battery was too short
reviews.reviewText: Although I have only ran the bike once, the chrome battery works great. It gave the bike plenty of its power back. I rated a 4 rather than 5 because the battery was not an exact fit for the 1994 Honda Magna as advertised. It was shorter than the original which made it to where the cables would not fit. Easy fix tho I just folded a piece of cardboard put it under the battery to make it sit taller and away we went

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got this as a replacement for the battery in my 92 XJ600 Seca II, after the battery wouldn't hold a charge after winter storage. Not al to to say, except it fits, and it works. Recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Check the sizing
reviews.reviewText: Battery works great. Starts my bike, runs great. It does not actually fit in the battery box on my Honda 919, but it went in with a heat gun. I made that choice to get a few more cold cranking amps, but I’m guessing some people will not want to make that modification.
